### Certificate API Testing
### Make sure your server is running on http://localhost:3000

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@token = YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### 1. Login to get JWT token (replace with your credentials)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/mobile/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 2. Get Transaction Certificate
### Replace {transactionId} with an actual transaction ID from your database
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/mobile/certificates/transactions/{{transactionId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 3. Get Property Legal Document
### Replace {propertyId} with an actual property ID from your database
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/mobile/certificates/properties/{{propertyId}}/legal-document
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 4. Generate Portfolio Summary Certificate
### Replace {propertyId} with an actual property ID where user has investments
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/mobile/certificates/portfolio/{{propertyId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5. Make an Investment (to trigger auto-certificate generation)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/mobile/investments
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "propertyId": "your-property-id",
  "tokenCount": 2.5
}

